Three U.S. citizens to be tried on Nov. 6
TEHRAN â€“ The three U.S. citizens who were arrested in Iran last year will stand trial on November 6, their attorney Masoud Shafiee said on Saturday.
Shane Bauer, 27, Sarah Shourd, 31, and Josh Fattal, 27, were arrested in July last year on suspicion of spying after they illegally entered Iran. Shourd was released from prison on a bail of $500,000 last month. Their trial will be held at 10:00 a.m. local time in the Revolution Court, branch 15, Shafiee told IRNA news agency. Shafiee said neither him nor his clients have admitted the charges